The paper discusses the use of deep learning in software analytics, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also compares the performance of deep learning with a simpler optimizer, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Stack Overflow data for analysis suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of computational cost and optimization suggests a potential focus on software development (cs.SD) as well.
